'''''Star Wars Galaxies: Jump to Lightspeed''''' was the first expansion pack to the [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]''. [[Sony]] Online Entertainment released the expansion on [[October 27]], [[2004]].

==Contents==
This expansion finally allowed players to explore and battle in ten sectors of outer space, in more than twenty types of starships from the era between [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], including familiar [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wings]], [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE Fighters]], and [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300s]] (same type as the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]), as well as new and never before seen ships created by the developers. It also added real-time space shooter elements to the game, which allowed for an interesting combination with the turn-based mode already featured in the ground-based. ''Jump to Lightspeed'' also added many space missions and four space-specific professions. Two races were also added: [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustan]] and [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]].
The expansion added space combat. Characters could choose one of three factions in the new Pilot sub-profession: [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]], [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]], or Freelance. The playable sectors include the space surrounding the ten planets of the game as well as [[Kessel/Legends|Kessel]] and "Deep Space." Combat is real-time and twitch-oriented like a [[Wikipedia:First-person shooter|first-person shooter]] and can be played with a joystick at the player's option. A new Artisan profession, Shipwright, was also introduced. This profession created ships, shields, armor, weapons, etc for players. They also have the ability to take looted components from space and reverse engineer them into better components.

''Jump to Lightspeed'' is now automatically included upon the installation of the game, regardless of which version.

==Boxed Set {{SectionFlag|1}}==
Before ''Jump to Lightspeed'' was made to be automatically installed into the game regardless of which version, it was sold in a box set. Customers who pre-ordered the expansion received a limited-edition unarmed [[Seraph-class urban landspeeder|Flash Speeder]] as an untradeable player vehicle. After this boxed set, the expansion was eventually added to [[Star Wars Galaxies: The Total Experience|''The Total Experience'']] compilation pack.

